# Video Detection Pipeline

This project performs **face detection** and/or **object detection** on videos using YOLOv8. It generates annotated videos and saves detection results in CSV format.

---

```markdown
##  Project Structure
video/
├── src/
│   ├── main.py              # Main pipeline orchestrator
│   ├── main_time.py         # Same as main.py but with timing info
│   ├── preprocess_video.py  # 5fps conversion & stabilization
│   ├── segment_video.py     # Video segmentation (60s chunks)
│   ├── face_detect.py       # Face detection (YOLOv5-face)
│   └── object_detect.py     # Object detection (YOLOv8)
├── input_videos/            # Place your input videos here (.mp4 or .mov)
├── results/                 # Output directory
│   └── {version_name}/      # e.g., "with_stab_with_seg"
│       ├── segments/        # If segmentation used
│       ├── detections/      # Detection results per segment
│       └── *_merged_detections.csv
├── preprocessed_5fps/       # Cached 5fps videos
├── yolov8s.pt              # YOLOv8 model weights
└── requirements.txt


##  How to Run the Pipeline

### 1. Set Up Virtual Environment
cd video
python -m venv venv
# Mac/Linux source venv/bin/activate      # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate

### 2. Install Requirements
pip install -r requirements.txt

### 3. Add Video(s)

### 4. Run the Pipeline
python src/main.py

### Output

Annotated videos:  
results/runs/<face_detect|object_detect>/<video_name>.mp4

CSV results:  
results/csv/<face_detect_results|object_detect_results>.csv

Each CSV contains:  
frame_number,object_class,confidence_score,x1,y1,x2,y2


